main event: A ground-radar observation reported a single unexplained object in Liconnville, Maine on December 23, 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as flashing and wide in the rear,The object emitted a flashing green light without any sound,The sighting lasted only a few seconds,The observation was conducted via ground-radar,There was an earlier associated investigation conducted on December 21, 1954 that included a photograph.
